            <input type="radio" id="q1d" name="q1" value="All of the above">
            <label for="qid">All of the above</label><br>

            <li>What is Tezos’s native token called?</li>
            <input type="radio" id="q2a" name="q2" value="Tez">
            <label for="q2a">Tez</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q2b" name="q2" value="Tezzy">
            <label for="q2b">Tezzy</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q2c" name="q2" value="Tezzie">
            <label for="q2c">Tezzie</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q2d" name="q2" value="Tezas">
            <label for="q2d">Tezas</label><br>

            

            <li>What is staking in Tezos called?</li>
            <input type="radio" id="q3a" name="q3" value="Packing">
            <label for="q3a">Packing</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q3b" name="q3" value="Stacking">
            <label for="q3b">Stacking</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q3c" name="q3" value="Forging">
            <label for="q3c">Forging</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q3d" name="q3" value="Baking">
            <label for="q3d">Baking</label><br>

            

            <li>What is Tezos’s proof of stake mechanism called?</li>
            <input type="radio" id="q4a" name="q4" value="Solid Proof of Stake">
            <label for="4qa">Solid Proof of Stake</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q4b" name="q4" value="Delegated Proof of Stake">
            <label for="4qb">Delegated Proof of Stake</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q4c" name="q4" value="Liquid Proof of Stake">
            <label for="4qc">Liquid Proof of Stake</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q4d" name="q4" value="Gas Proof of Stake">
            <label for="4qd">Gas Proof of Stake</label><br>

            

            <li>Which one of the following is Tezos machine level language?</li>
            <input type="radio" id="q5a" name="q5" value="Albeit">
